Subject: ask: migrate OOT source into in-tree drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/

PR14z19 Path A stage 2 of the in-tree migration plan
(plans/PR14z19-PATH-A-DESIGN.md and the agent-session stages 1-6
plan).  Stage 1 (patch 0047) created the in-tree directory with a
single fs_initcall banner.  This stage replaces that skeleton with
the full ASK2 source migrated from the legacy out-of-tree tree at
kernel/flavors/ask/oot-modules/ask/.

Migration map (OOT path -> in-tree path):

  kernel/flavors/ask/oot-modules/ask/ask_main.c
    -> drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_main.c
  kernel/flavors/ask/oot-modules/ask/ask_hw.c
    -> drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_hw.c    (1544 LOC)
  kernel/flavors/ask/oot-modules/ask/ask_flow_offload.c
    -> drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_flow_offload.c (1862 LOC)
  kernel/flavors/ask/oot-modules/ask/ask_genl.c
    -> drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_genl.c   (534 LOC)
  kernel/flavors/ask/oot-modules/ask/ask_flow.c
    -> drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_flow.c   (543 LOC)
  kernel/flavors/ask/oot-modules/ask/ask_genl_attr.c
    -> drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_genl_attr.c (100 LOC)
  kernel/flavors/ask/oot-modules/ask/ask_xfrm.c
    -> drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_xfrm.c    (38 LOC)
  kernel/flavors/ask/oot-modules/ask/ask_{op,stats,debugfs,neigh,bridge,caam}.c
    -> drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_{op,stats,debugfs,neigh,bridge,caam}.c
       (21 LOC stubs each — PR1-skeleton lifecycle hooks)
  kernel/flavors/ask/oot-modules/ask/ask_trace.h
    -> drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_trace.h
  kernel/flavors/ask/oot-modules/ask/include/ask_internal.h
    -> drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_internal.h (flattened)
  kernel/flavors/ask/oot-modules/ask/include/uapi/linux/ask/ask.h
    -> include/uapi/linux/ask/ask.h (moved to kernel-standard uapi tree)

Source-file deltas vs OOT verbatim copy:

  1. All "#include \"include/ask_internal.h\"" rewrites to
     "#include \"ask_internal.h\"" (the include/ subdir is dropped
     because in-tree convention is flat per-driver layout).

  2. ask_internal.h gains one missing prototype:
     "int ask_xfrm_state_add(struct xfrm_state *x);"  This silences
     the -Wmissing-prototypes warning that the in-tree build catches
     but the OOT Kbuild did not (OOT builds use -Wno-missing-prototypes
     by default; the in-tree build enforces it).

  3. ask_main.c is currently the OOT verbatim copy — it still uses
     module_init()/module_exit() rather than fs_initcall().  For a
     built-in driver (CONFIG_FSL_DPAA_ASK=y) module_init expands to
     device_initcall, which is functionally identical to the OOT
     behaviour but is structurally too late for the pre-netdev hook.
     Patch 0049 (stage 3) rewrites ask_init() to call
     fman_pcd_register_pre_netdev_hook() under fs_initcall.

  4. The OOT Kbuild's "obj-$(CONFIG_NET_ASK) += ask.o" is replaced by
     the in-tree Makefile's "obj-$(CONFIG_FSL_DPAA_ASK) += ask.o".
     The ask-y / ask-objs list is mirrored verbatim (14 objects, in
     the same init-call order as in ask_main.c).

The uapi header moves to the kernel-standard include/uapi/linux/ask/
location so #include <uapi/linux/ask/ask.h> Just Works without any
-I flag wrangling.  ask_genl.c and ask_genl_attr.c reference it via
the standard angle-bracket include path.

